{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Shape2D"],"type":"inheritsFrom"},{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D\/points"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D\/setPointCloud(_:)"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D\/godotClassName"],"title":"Type Properties"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A 2D convex polygon shape used for physics collision."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ConvexPolygonShape2D","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A 2D convex polygon shape, intended for use in physics. Used internally in ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CollisionPolygon2D","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" when it’s in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CollisionPolygon2D\/BuildMode\/buildSolids"},{"text":" mode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"solid","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", which means it detects collisions from objects that are fully inside it, unlike "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConcavePolygonShape2D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" which is hollow. This makes it more suitable for both detection and physics."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Convex decomposition:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" A concave polygon can be split up into several convex polygons. This allows dynamic physics bodies to have complex concave collisions (at a performance cost) and can be achieved by using several "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" nodes or by using the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CollisionPolygon2D","type":"reference"},{"text":" node in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CollisionPolygon2D\/BuildMode\/buildSolids"},{"text":" mode. To generate a collision polygon from a sprite, select the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Sprite2D","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" node, go to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sprite2D"}]},{"type":"text","text":" menu that appears above the viewport, and choose "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create Polygon2D Sibling"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","tex